{{Infobox book | italic title = <!--(see above)--> | name = Another Man's War | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | author = [[Sam Childers]] | audio_read_by = | title_orig = | orig_lang_code = | title_working = | translator = | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = United States | language = English | series = | release_number = | subject = | set_in = | publisher = [[Thomas Nelson (publisher)|Thomas Nelson]] | publisher2 = | pub_date = 2009 | english_pub_date = | published = | media_type = Print | pages = | awards = | isbn = | isbn_note = | oclc = | dewey = | congress = | preceded_by = | followed_by = | native_wikisource = | wikisource = | notes = | exclude_cover = | website = }}
'''''Another Man's War''''' is a 2009 book written by [[Sam Childers]] about his life as a former [[outlaw motorcycle club|gang biker]] turned preacher and defender of South Sudanese orphans.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[Google Books]]|date=2009|title=Another Man's War|author=Childers, Sam|authorlink=Sam Childers|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=rURMuShddjYC&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_ge_summary_r&cad=0#v=onepage&q&f=false}}</ref>
The book was the basis of ''[[Machine Gun Preacher]]'', a 2011 [[Biographical film|biographical]] [[Adventure film|adventure]] [[drama (film and television)|drama film]] starring [[Gerard Butler]].<ref name=London>{{cite web|url=http://www.thisislondon.co.uk/film/review-24006020-machine-gun-preacher---review.do|title=Machine Gun Preacher - review|work=London Evening Standard|date=4 November 2011|accessdate=4 November 2011}}</ref>
The book bears the endorsement from South Sudan President [[Salva Kiir Mayardit]], "The Reverend Sam Childers has been a very close friend to the government of South Sudan for many years and is a trusted friend."<ref>{{cite web|title=Another Mans War: The True Story of One Mans Battle to Save Children in the Sudan|date=March 17, 2009|publisher=Amazon|author=Sam Childers}}</ref>
