'''''First People: A Documentary Survey of American Indian History''''' was written by [[Colin G. Calloway]] (born 1953), a British historian.  He is the professor of [[Native American Studies at Dartmouth College]].  The book's most recent edition was published by Bedford/St.Martin's on September 2, 2015 and the first edition was published in 2004.  The book provides an overview of perspectives of [[Native Americans in the United States|American Indian history]] through Calloway's own research of both Native Indians and European colonials along with primary source documents and picture essays.

