'''Post-Futurism''' (alternatively '''Postfuturism''') is a term coined by [[Vivian Sobchack]] to describe certain [[science fiction films]] of the late 1970s and early 1980s,<ref>Vivian Sobchack, ''Screening Space: The American Science Fiction Film'', Rutgers University Press, 1997, p. 223. {{ISBN|0-8135-2492-X}}</ref> a [[genre]] of [[science fiction]],{{Citation needed|date=January 2008}} an [[art movement|artistic movement]],{{Citation needed|date=January 2008}} and an architectural movement.{{Citation needed|date=January 2008}} In the past the term has been used as a synonym for [[Postmodernism]].<ref>Raymond Federman, ''Critifiction: Postmodern Essays'', SUNY Press, 1993, p. 129. {{ISBN|0-7914-1679-8}}</ref>

